			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think necros get crit heals more for themselves than their pets.  The pet heals are just a bonus.
<br />

<br />
I personally hate chain summoning.  I prefer to equip and buff my pet and use that one.  I want a more powerful pet that doesn't need better heals.  Even though I don't chain, I'd really like to see a beastlord even try and chain pets as well as I can.  I have a larger mana pool, conjuration specialized, Spell Casting Mastery 3, and Quick Summoning 3.  So how is it again that they can do it as well as mages?
<br />

<br />
Also, how is it that beastlords have superior haste?  We have the best haste in the game (85%).  Combined with the muzzel (11%), that's 96% haste, practically at the haste cap.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
